<SLUG> BC-ERNESTMURRAY-COLUMN08-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Test this test, please
 &HT;    By Ernest Murray
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   LUFKIN, Texas _ Think you just have to be born between World War
II and the 1960s to qualify as a baby boomer? According to this
e-mail I received, there's a qualifying exam to take before you can
become a full-fledged boomer. While not as complicated as the Mensa
test, it does touch on everything from music and politics to sports
and TV. And in keeping with the boomer philosophy, there's no
points off for wrong answers.
</P>
<P>
   1. Name the Beatles.
</P>
<P>
   2. What do M&AMP;M's do?
</P>
<P>
   3. What helps build strong bodies 12 ways?
</P>
<P>
   4. Bob Dylan advised us never to trust anyone over what age?
</P>
<P>
   5. Before he was Mohammed Ali, who was he known as?
</P>
<P>
   6. He came out of the University of Alabama, and became one of
the best quarterbacks in the history of the NFL. He later went on
to appear in a television commercial wearing women's pantyhose. Who
is he?
</P>
<P>
   7. Finish the line: ``Lions and tigers and bears, ...!''
(Admittedly, this came along before boomers were born. But it was
on TV every year.)
</P>
<P>
   8 ``Hey kids, what time is it?''
</P>
<P>
   9. Post-baby boomers know Bob Denver as the Skipper's ``little
buddy.'' But boomers know that Bob Denver is actually Dobie's
closest friend. Name him.
</P>
<P>
   10. Superman fights a never-ending battle for truth, justice,
and ...
</P>
<P>
   11. Your children probably recall that Peter Pan was recently
played by Robin Williams, but Peter was most memorably played by
whom?
</P>
<P>
   12. In 1962, a dejected politician chastised the press after
losing a race for governor while announcing his retirement from
politics. ``Just think, you won't have (who?) to kick around
anymore.''
</P>
<P>
   Finish these familiar sayings.
</P>
<P>
   13. ``You'll wonder where the yellow went ...''
</P>
<P>
   14. M-I-C: See ya' real soon; K-E-Y: ...''
</P>
<P>
   15. ``Brylcream: A little dab'll ...''
</P>
<P>
   16. ``I wonder, wonder, wonder, wonder who; ...''
</P>
<P>
   17. ``War, uh-huh, huh. Yeh; what is it good for? ...''
</P>
<P>
   18. ``I'm Popeye the sailor man; I'm Popeye the sailor man. I'm
strong to the finish, 'cause ...''
</P>
<P>
   19. ``I found my thrill ...''
</P>
<P>
   20. ``Good night, David.'' ``...''
</P>
<P>
   21. ``Liar, liar ...''
</P>
<P>
   22. ``When it's least expected, you're elected; You're the star
today. Smile! ...''
</P>
<P>
   23. It was Pogo, the comic strip character, who said, ``We have
met the enemy, and ...''
</P>
<P>
   24. ``Every morning, at the mine, you could see him arrive; He
stood 6-foot-6, weighted 245. Kinda' broad at the shoulder, and
narrow at the hip. And everybody knew you didn't give no lip to
...''
</P>
<P>
   25. In a movie from the late sixties, Paul Newman played Luke, a
ne'er do well who was sent to a prison camp for cutting off the
heads of parking meters with a pipe cutter. When he was captured
after an unsuccessful attempt to escape, the camp commander (played
by Strother Martin) used this experience as a lesson for the other
prisoners, and explained, ``What we have here ...''
</P>
<P>
   ANSWERS
</P>
<P>
   1. John, Paul, George, Ringo; 2. They melt in your mouth, not in
your hand.; 3. Wonder Bread; 4. 30; 5. Cassius Clay; 6. Joe Namath;
7. oh, my; 8. It's Howdy Doody Time!; 9. Maynard G. Krebbs; 10. the
American way; 11. Mary Martin; 12. Richard Nixon; 13. when you
brush your teeth with Pepsodent.; 14. Why? Because we like you.;
15. do ya.; 16. who wrote the book of love; 17. Absolutely nothin';
18. I eats me spinach; 19. on Blueberry Hill; 20. Good night, Chet;
21. pants on fire; 22. You're on Candid Camera; 23. he is us; 24.
Big Bad John; 25. is a failure to communicate.
</P>
<P>
   Ernest Murray is managing editor of The Lufkin Daily News.
E-mail: emurray(at)coxnews.com.
</P>
