<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    We've got a bone to Pika
 &HT;    By Gregory Kallenberg
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ It was one of the hottest toys of the Christmas
season and now it takes its place as the Annoying Gadget of the
Week. It's Hasbro's Interactive Pikachu Plush. If you haven't
experienced this toy, consider yourself lucky. If you have
experienced this toy, you know how cute it is at first. The rotund
yellow toy's cheeks glow red and it coos Pika, Pika ... chuuuuuu!
or Pikachu! or Pika?Chu? Pikachu! This continues until you go
insane or rip the stuffing out of everyone's favorite Pokemon
character. You can find the Interactive Pikachu Plush in little
children's hands all across America. The critters have been seen in
restaurants, on buses and in movie theaters. My advice to anyone
who sees those little red, glowing cheeks or hears the cursed
Pikachu!: Run, run for your life.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
