<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Behind the scenes of e-commerce
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Have you ever wondered how e-commerce really works?
The February issue of Business 2.0 offers a behind-the-scenes look
at the nuts and bolts. It examines how and why the best sites work,
offering helpful suggestions to companies just entering electronic
commerce or trying to improve their initial efforts.
</P>
<P>
   You've heard the shorthand _ MP3 _ but do you know what it
really means? Find out in the February issue of MacWorld magazine
how MP3 technology could change the way you listen to and obtain
music. The magazine's cover article discusses what MP3 music is,
how to get it and the new devices designed to play MP3 files.
</P>
<P>
   ON CD-ROM
</P>
<P>
   Activision has released the sequel to its popular game,
Battlezone. The new game is called Battlezone II: Combat Commander.
In this sequence, players become junior combat officers in the
International Space Defense Force. The game lets you control every
aspect of the battlefield, from building outposts to piloting tanks
and aircraft.
</P>
<P>
   Battlezone II is available only for PCs with Windows 95 or
higher. It retails for a suggested price of $50.
</P>
<P>
   Trickstyle is a new game set in the distant future that features
an activity called gravity surfing. Gravity surfing consists of
using a high-tech skateboard that lets you cruise above city
streets. In Trickstyle, you race against a variety of competitors
through a city of the future.
</P>
<P>
   Available only for PCs with Windows 95 and higher, Trickstyle
retails for a suggested price of $45.
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE
</P>
<P>
   Photobetty is a site dedicated to women photographers. It's
actually something called an e-zine, or a magazine published only
online. The site not only features work from women photographers
but is a resource.
</P>
<P>
   You can also submit your own work to be posted on the site.
You'll find Photobetty at www.photobetty.com.
</P>
