<HEADLINE>
PETER MAX IS ON TARGET
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Pop artist Peter Max is opening his latest exhibit to rave
reviews at an unconventional ``gallery'' this month. Max's designs,
both new and old, appear on a new line of greeting cards, gift
wrap, tissue paper and gift bags in several shapes, sizes and
styles at Target stores.
</P>
<P>
   The paper goods feature images from Max's famous ``cosmic '60s''
style as well as his bright ``neo-fauve'' paintings reflecting
different styles and artistic periods. Designs include the artist's
popular ``Umbrella Man'' and ``Dega Man,'' as well as his widely
known heart and angel motifs, just in time to wrap a special
Valentine's Day present.
</P>
<P>
   The new paper goods are available from $1.49 to $4.49.
</P>
</TEXT>
