<HEADLINE>
ROLL OUT THE RED FLOWER CARPET
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Anthony Tesselaar International has introduced the fourth in its
series of Flower Carpet easy-care groundcover roses. Red Flower
Carpet, which blooms from spring through fall and has a natural
resistance to black spot and mildew, joins pink (introduced in
1995), white (1997) and appleblossom (1998) varieties.
</P>
<P>
   The red, single 2-inch blossoms have prominent golden stamens
and glossy green foliage. The ruffled blooms cascade over the pot
or along the ground. And unlike most other roses, Red Flower Carpet
doesn't require routine dusting or spraying, tricky pruning,
dead-heading or special handling, just water, fertilizer and a good
cutback in late winter or early spring.
</P>
<P>
   A well-fed, well-watered, mature bush can produce up to 2,000
flowers in a season. Look for it to be priced between $12 and $16
at home and garden centers.
</P>
</TEXT>
