<HEADLINE>
`THE ART OF THE DOLLMAKER'
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL BIDWELL 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Learn what's involved in making dolls, from the mass-marketed
Barbie to handcrafted, one-of-a-kind works of art in ``The Art of
the Doll Maker,'' a one-hour, 19-minute videotape that includes
interviews with famed doll makers and visits to their studios.
</P>
<P>
   Artists whose works are featured include E.J. Taylor, Lisa
Lichtenfels, Elinor Peace Bailey, Charlene Westling and more. More
than 160 dolls are shown, along with the stories of the creation of
many of them.
</P>
<P>
   The tape is available for $29.95, plus $4.50 shipping and
handling, by calling (888) 880-8365 or writing PMB 1105, 369 S.
Doheny Drive, Beverly Hills, Calif. 90211. For more information,
call Choices Inc. at (310) 360-8500.
