<P>
   &QL; 
PRESCRIBE (Undated) - Rural Arizona seniors are up in arms about
lack of HMO coverage. Some are moving to Maricopa County, others
are desperately trying to figure out what to do: Pay their rent or
by their drugs. Only five of the counties in Arizona now have HMO
coverage, And the rural counties that do still have HMOs have cut
back services. By MAUREEN WEST. Story will move in the `A`
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
SEDONA (Undated) - The U.S. Forest Service is about to start
charging for hiking the red rocks of the Sedona area as part of its
fee program to recoup money for the local Forest Service offices.
The likely fee will be $20 per year or $5 a visit. This hasn't gone
down well in the Sedona area. It also was a hot potato when the
Prescott National Forest did this last year for hiking in the
Prescott area. By MARK SHAFFER. Story will move in the `A`
category. &QL; 
