<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PEANUTS-TIMELINE13-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   Peanuts timeline: Snoopy's evolution to a higher plane
</P>
<P>
   (With PEANUTS-APPRECIATION. Embargoed for Sunday, Feb. 13.)
</P>
<P>
   By Frank C. Rizzo
</P>
<P>
   c 2000 Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   This timeline of the ``Peanuts'' comic strip includes the first
appearances of characters (in capital letters) and descriptions of
major story lines and recurring themes.
</P>
<P>
   ``Snoopy as:'' indicates the first time Snoopy imagines himself
in a given role.
</P>
<P>
   The timeline is based in large part on research by Derrick Bang,
whose ``50 Years of Happiness: A Tribute to Charles M. Schulz''
will be published in limited edition this year. For more details,
see the Peanuts Collector Club site, www.peanutscollectorclub.com.
</P>
<P>
   1950: ``Peanuts'' debuts Oct. 2, with CHARLIE BROWN, SHERMY and
PATTY. SNOOPY follows in the third strip. Later, Charlie Brown
wears his zigzag sweater.
</P>
<P>
   1951: VIOLET and SCHROEDER (as a baby).
</P>
<P>
   1952: Sunday strip begins Jan. 6. LUCY VAN PELT debuts as a
wide-eyed toddler, but grows quickly enough to get a brother,
LINUS, later in the year. Charlie Brown is called ''wishy-washy''
(by Violet and Patty). Snoopy as: a go-cart motor.
</P>
<P>
   1953: Lucy falls in love with Schroeder.
</P>
<P>
   1954: Linus gets his security blanket. PIG-PEN and CHARLOTTE
BRAUN (a loud, anti-Charlie Brown who fades away once Lucy takes on
those characteristics). Snoopy's doghouse begins growing internally
_ it has a recreation room and five kids pile in. Charlie Brown and
Lucy lean against a wall for the first time while talking. Snoopy
as: a shark (in a wading pool).
</P>
<P>
   1955: Linus goes through withdrawal while his blanket is being
washed. Snoopy as: a wolf, a rhinoceros, a snake, a pelican, Lucy,
Violet, Beethoven and Mickey Mouse.
</P>
<P>
   1956: Charlie Brown's kite lands in a tree. Snoopy dances on his
back feet. Snoopy as: a giraffe, kangaroo, alligator, lion and
elephant.
</P>
<P>
   1957: Linus tries to kick the blanket habit. Snoopy as: a polar
bear, bird, mule, circus dog, sea monster and penguin.
</P>
<P>
   1958: Charlie Brown drops a fly ball and becomes ``the goat''
instead of the hero, writes his first pen-pal letter and is called
``you blockhead'' (by Lucy, of course). Snoopy stands on two legs.
Snoopy as: an anteater, bald eagle, vulture, tiger and goat.
</P>
<P>
   1959: Charlie Brown gets a sister, SALLY. Lucy opens a
lemonade-stand psychiatric booth (``Psychiatric help, 5 cents'').
Linus believes in the GREAT PUMPKIN. Snoopy as: Big Man on Campus
(an early Joe Cool), bloodhound, cow, human baby, cricket and
mountain lion.
</P>
<P>
   1960: Linus mentions his blanket-hating ``gramma.'' Sally takes
her first steps and forms a crush on Linus. Snoopy as: TV antenna,
Whirlidog (an early helicopter), dinosaur and ``The Mad Punter.''
</P>
<P>
   1961: FRIEDA (with the naturally curly hair), and her very limp
cat, FARON. The Little Red-Haired Girl is mentioned. Snoopy as:
ship's captain, rabbit, gorilla and lost calf.
</P>
<P>
   1962: Sally gets her first look at school _ and runs. Snoopy
climbs onto his doghouse roof to sleep under the moon, claiming ``I
can't sleep without a night light.'' Schulz begins depicting the
doghouse only from the side. Snoopy as: jungle ape, shepherd,
gargoyle and teddy bear.
</P>
<P>
   1963: The boy named ``5'' is introduced (full name: 555 95472),
with his little sisters, ``3'' and ``4.'' 5 says the advent of ZIP
codes made his father believe everyone will be known by numbers.
Charlie Brown balks in the tying and winning runs and loses the
championship game. Snoopy as: a weather vane.
</P>
<P>
   1964: Linus paints mural on ceiling of doghouse. First mention
of Snoopy's Van Gogh painting. Lucy gives Charlie Brown a slide
show of his many faults, and then bills him for $143. Lucy's
science fair project _ seeing how long Linus can go without his
security blanket _ wins first prize. Snoopy as: an ice-skating
champion, a sheep and a partridge in a pear tree.
</P>
<P>
   1965: Charlie Brown meets a lonesome ROY at summer camp and
becomes his friend. Snoopy as: a trapeze artist, skateboard
champion, bowling ace, an author (''It was a dark and stormy
night''), Lucy's assistant psychiatrist, a surfer, and the World
War I flying ace.
</P>
<P>
   1966: Linus commands an army of snowmen. Linus goes to summer
camp and meets Roy, who introduces him to PEPPERMINT PATTY (real
name: Patricia Reichardt). Later, Peppermint Patty comes across
town to manage Charlie Brown's baseball team (she thinks Snoopy is
``the funny looking kid with the big nose.'') Snoopy's doghouse
burns down. The new doghouse includes ceramic tile and a stairway,
and the lost Van Gogh is replaced with an Andrew Wyeth. Snoopy as:
a soldier of the French Foreign Legion and World War I Army
Surgeon.
</P>
<P>
   1967: WOODSTOCK (as yet unnamed) flutters into Snoopy's
doghouse. Lucy challenges the gang at arm wrestling, and always
wins until ``The Masked Marvel'' (Snoopy) bests her. Snoopy goes to
the arm wrestling championships in Petaluma, Calif., but is
disqualified _ he has no thumbs. Snoopy as Masked Marvel, a
piranha, a ``Cheshire beagle,'' a secret agent (hired by Linus to
find his missing blanket) and the World-Famous Hockey Player.
</P>
<P>
   1968: Charlie Brown meets FRANKLIN at the beach. Peppermint
Patty meets CLARA (an early version of Marcie) at summer camp.
Charlie Brown finds out he has a ``used dog'' _ months before he
got Snoopy at the Daisy Hill Puppy Farm, Snoopy was adopted by
LILA's family, then returned because they lived in an apartment.
Linus rebels when his beloved Miss Othmar is fired in a teachers'
strike. Snoopy as a monster-movie ``creature from the sea,'' school
principal, baseball manager, the World-Famous Golf Pro, the Easter
Beagle and the World-Famous Wrist Wrestler.
</P>
<P>
   1969: Snoopy becomes Peppermint Patty's skating partner. Last
appearance of Shermy (Patty and Violet occasionally pop up in crowd
scenes into the '90s). Snoopy as: Captain of the Rescue Squad, a
prairie dog, the World-Famous Astronaut (who lands on the moon),
the tether-ball champion, the World-Famous Roller Derby Star, the
World-Famous Baseball Superstar, the World-Famous Football Star,
the WWII Veteran and the World-Famous Skier.
</P>
<P>
   1970: Woodstock gets his name. Frieda reports Snoopy to the Head
Beagle for refusing to chase rabbits. Later, Snoopy becomes Head
Beagle (with Woodstock as his secretary), then escapes his workload
by fleeing to Peppermint Patty's house. Charlie Brown buys tickets
to a sports banquet so he can sit with his baseball hero, Joe
Shlabotnik _ who never shows up. Snoopy is invited to the Daisy
Hill Puppy Farm to give a July 4 speech, and a riot breaks out.
Snoopy as: Head Beagle and the World-Famous Grocery Clerk.
</P>
<P>
   1971: MARCIE meets Peppermint Patty _ and calls her ``sir'' _ at
summer camp. Snoopy as: sheep dog, Joe Cool, the World-Famous
Football Coach and the World-Famous Swimmer.
</P>
<P>
   1972: Lucy and Linus get a little brother, Rerun (who is not yet
seen). Linus finds out that Miss Helen Sweetstory's latest book,
``The Six Bunny-Wunnies Freak Out,'' has been banned from the
school library by the school board, led by Charlie Brown's
pediatrician. Snoopy learns the Daisy Hill Puppy Farm has been
replaced by a six-story parking garage. Snoopy as: the world-famous
attorney, captain of the Starship Enterprise, a fierce pirate and a
bat.
</P>
<P>
   1973: RERUN is introduced. Suffering from a baseball obsession,
Charlie Brown is sent to summer camp to rest. He wears a bag over
his head to hide a rash that looks like baseball stitching. To his
surprise, ``Mr. Sack'' is elected camp president and the other
campers respect him _ until he removes the bag. While Peppermint
Patty's father is out of town, she stays in Charlie Brown's ``guest
cottage'' (Snoopy's doghouse). Snoopy as the World-Famous Tennis
Star.
</P>
<P>
   1974: Sally talks to her school _ and the building replies in
thought balloons. Rerun rides on a bicycle behind his mother. Fed
up with school, Peppermint Patty decides to stay forever on the
doghouse with Snoopy. A frustrated Marcie pulls them down,
destroying the doghouse, and tells Patty to ``face up to reality''
_ the ``guest cottage'' is a doghouse and Snoopy is a beagle. The
Beagle Scouts birds are shown. (One is Woodstock, and in 1978 we
learn the others are CONRAD, OLIVIER and BILL. HARRIET joins in
1980). Snoopy as: the Pawpet Theater Host, a streaker, the Beagle
Scout (a tenderpaw), and the World-Famous Crabby Skating Pro.
</P>
<P>
   1975: Snoopy's older brother SPIKE visits from Needles, Calif.
Lucy serves him milkshakes to fatten him up. Linus meets and falls
for TRUFFLES. Last appearance of Frieda. Snoopy as: Joe Motocross,
airplane mechanic and ``man from the Chamber of Commerce.''
</P>
<P>
   1976: The gang's school falls down during the night and they
have to go to another school across town; Charlie Brown ends up
sharing Peppermint Patty's desk. Snoopy goes off to play at
Wimbledon but stops in Kansas City to see his sister, BELLE, and
her teenage son. Peppermint Patty transfers to a private school
recommended by Snoopy _ the Ace Obedience School. She graduates
before she finds out her mistake, then seeks revenge. She attacks
the cat who lives next door (she thinks it's Snoopy in a cat suit),
and Snoopy goes to her rescue. Snoopy as: the World-Famous Jogger.
</P>
<P>
   1977: Sally calls Linus her ``Sweet Babboo.'' Snoopy gets a
foul-tempered tennis partner, MOLLY VOLLEY. Snoopy as: a
helicopter, a crop-duster, an owl and Peppermint Patty (a
disguise).
</P>
<P>
   1978: Sally meets EUDORA on the way to summer camp. Eudora gives
Linus' blanket to the cat next door, and Snoopy (as a helicopter)
drops Linus and himself on the cat. A fight erupts, and Woodstock
recovers the blanket. Snoopy as: a traffic copter and World-Famous
Disco Dancer.
</P>
<P>
   1979: Charlie Brown is hospitalized. His friends worry; Lucy
even vows not to pull the football away if he'll only get better.
Recovered, Charlie Brown holds her to her promise. He runs at the
ball, Lucy does NOT pull it away ... but Charlie Brown misses it
and kicks her arm instead. Snoopy as: The April Fool, Blackjack
Snoopy (World-Famous Riverboat Gambler), the World-Famous County
Surveyor, a scarecrow and a fierce python.
</P>
<P>
   1980: Snoopy as: a bow-and-arrow hunter, Dr. Beagle and Mr.
Hyde, a fierce rattlesnake, the World-Famous Census Taker, John
McEnroe, Tracy Austin, John Newcombe and a Zamboni driver.
</P>
<P>
   1981: Snoopy as: a portrait painter, Joe Preppy.
</P>
<P>
   1982: Snoopy's brother MARBLES appears. Snoopy as: the
World-Famous Hired Hand, the World-Famous Surgeon and Joe
Sandbagger (while bowling).
</P>
<P>
   1983: Snoopy as: an Olympic chariot racer and Flashbeagle.
</P>
<P>
   1985: Snoopy as: The Little Red-Haired Girl and ''Punk'' Beagle.
</P>
<P>
   1986: Linus has a big crush on schoolmate LYDIA, who calls
herself by 10 other names, including ``Snowflake.'' TAPIOCA
PUDDING, whose father licenses everything about her, is Schulz's
inside joke on comic strips that exist solely to sell merchandise.
Snoopy as: the World-Famous Agent.
</P>
<P>
   1987: Eudora's last appearance. Snoopy as: Joe Aerobics.
</P>
<P>
   1989: Snoopy's fat brother, OLAF, wins an ``ugly dog'' contest.
Snoopy as: Alistair Beagle, ``Shoeless'' Joe Beagle and Santa
Claus.
</P>
<P>
   1990: Charlie Brown meets his summer camp sweetheart, PEGGY
JEAN, who calls him ``Brownie Charles.'' Snoopy as: tennis
ball-beagle and a fierce ``October beast.''
</P>
<P>
   1991: Sally kicks a boy out of her Bible class and later finds
out LARRY is the minister's son. Snoopy as: the World-Famous
Highway Flagman, a beaver, a school honor student and a trained
service technician.
</P>
<P>
   1992: Snoopy as: a wounded soldier, a ventriloquist and the
pilot for ``Ace Airlines'' (which Schroeder takes to get to music
camp. Marcie is the flight attendant).
</P>
<P>
   1993: Charlie Brown hits his first game-winning home run, but
his joy is dashed when he meets the losing _ and dejected _
pitcher, ROYANNE HOBBS, great-granddaughter of Roy Hobbs. Snoopy
as: Joe Grunge.
</P>
<P>
   1994: WOODSTOCK'S GRANDFATHER is seen by way of a diary. ANDY,
another of Snoopy's brothers, appears.
</P>
<P>
   1995: Charlie Brown meets EMILY, his occasional dance partner.
</P>
<P>
   1996: SNOOPY'S MOTHER is seen.
</P>
<P>
   1997: Snoopy as: a Revolutionary War Patriot and Blackbeagle,
World-Famous Pirate.
</P>
<P>
   1998: THE LITTLE RED-HAIRED GIRL makes her one and only
appearance, at a dance Charlie Brown is attending, but is shown
only in silhouette, dancing with Snoopy. JOE CACTUS, Spike's friend
in the desert, appears. Snoopy as: the World-Famous Big Rig
Operator and the (F.) Scott Fitzgerald Hero.
</P>
<P>
   1999: Snoopy as: a diving expert and the World-Famous Orthopedic
Surgeon.
</P>
<P>
   2000: The last daily strip runs on the first day of the year. It
shows Snoopy watching Charlie Brown and friends in a snowball
fight, with the caption: ``Suddenly the dog realized that his dad
had never taught him how to throw snowballs.'' The next Monday,
Jan. 3, Schulz says farewell to his readers. Sunday strips end
today.
</P>
<P>
   Frank C. Rizzo is comics editor for The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
