<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Tuesday, Feb. 8 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News at (818)
713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   SECOND-SIGHT (Pasadena, Calif.) _ Exectives of Second Sight, a
Mini-Med spinoff, pitched their electronic vision techology to
potential investors Monday at a bio-med investment meeting. By
Jason Cohen.
</P>
<P>
   KARLOFF-SUIT (Los Angeles) _ Sara Karloff, whose father
portrayed such classic horror characters as Frankenstein and The
Mummy, is asking for damages in excess of $10 million stemming from
what she says is Universal's unauthorized use of her father's
image. By Marla Matzer-Rose.
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Let the hire beware. Daily News
columnist Ken Lloyd, Ph.D., a specialist in organizational
behavior, answers readers' questions on workplace ethics and
relationships.
</P>
