<P>
   ALASKA-CRASH-FEAR (Seattle) _ Alaska Airlines and travel agents
say ``a handful'' of travelers have cancelled or changed travel
plans, but there's no rush away from the 1,200-or-so MD-80 planes
now in service. But among that handful is John Cook, a service
station owner from Sterling, Alaska, who delayed his departure for
home from Seattle by a day so he could fly another plane.
</P>
<P>
