combined company, which will be called Pfizer, becomes the
second-largest drug company in the world behind Glaxo Wellcome and
SmithKline Beecham. But because it also becomes the fastest-growing
pharmaceutical company, it is expected to overtake
Glaxo-SmithKline, the British drug giant created by Glaxo Wellcome
and SmithKline Beecham, which announced their merger plans last
month.
