<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STARR FOR MORE FULL DISCLOSURE
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Standing by while  &UR; John Dean &LR;  and  &UR; Kenneth Starr &LR;  chatted during
the lunch break after a Hastings Law Journal symposium about
Watergate on Saturday,  &UR; Jonathan Perdue &LR;  heard them discussing
Dean's assertion, during the morning proceedings, that he had
analyzed every bit of  &UR; Bob Woodward &LR;  and  &UR; Carl Bernstein &LR; 's ``All
the President's Men'' and determined that  &UR; Alexander Haig &LR;  was the
only possible Deep Throat.
</P>
<P>
   Although that rumor has been bandied about, Starr asked former
White House counsel Dean if he had ever revealed his conclusion in
public before. ``No,'' said Dean, ``that was the first time this
morning.''
</P>
<P>
   ``John, you owe America a book,'' said Starr.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; GEORGETTE MOSBACHER CHOOSES A CANDIDATE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Georgette Mosbacher &LR; , who used to be married to  &UR; George &LR; 
 &UR; Bush &LR; 's commerce secretary,  &UR; Robert Mosbacher &LR; , told the New York
Observer about her divorce and her support of Republican
presidential contender  &UR; John McCain &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   Her husband betrayed her for another woman, Mosbacher said. ``My
self-esteem hit the floor, and I felt scared and insecure, and I
felt unattractive, and I felt stupid, and I felt all those things
you go through. I felt lost. I felt really lost. It's as if someone
takes a hand grenade and throws it in the middle of your life.''
</P>
<P>
   She said she and McCain have been friends since 1988. ``I know
John, I admire John, I respect John. John turned 63 in September. I
knew that this was John's shot.'' Furthermore, she said, she was
moved by reading McCain's account of being a prisoner of war. ``I
think I was going through my darkest time, too.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HOLLYWOOD'S IDEA OF A `CERTAIN AGE' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Eleven British women between the ages of 45 and 66 have done
their own version of the full monty, posing nude for a 2000
calendar sold to raise money for cancer research. The calendar,
with its average-size women posing in pearls and strategically
placed props, has been a huge success; sales of 88,000 have raised
$500,000.
</P>
<P>
   Warner Bros. and Disney are bidding for movie rights to the
women's story. Said Miss May,  &UR; Moyra Livesey &LR; : ``We wouldn't want
anybody who's had a face-lift or a boob job, which would rule out
half of Hollywood. A British actress like  &UR; Julie Walters &LR;  is more
our cup of tea.''
</P>
<P>
   Hollywood's idea of a lead actress, says the BBC:  &UR; Meg Ryan &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SHOPPING LIST &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Virginia Leach &LR;  reports the first sighting of ads for next
Christmas, in Sunday ad sections tucked into the January 23 San
Francisco Chronicle &AMP; Examiner:
</P>
<P>
   Stained-glass window ornaments, a Berta Hummel Christmas,
adorable ballerina ornaments; and if you act now, you'll forget
where you stored them before it's time to take them out.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Catherine Hoffman &LR;  received a most romantic notice for
Valentine's Day, quoting Krishnamurti: ``The moment you have in
your heart this extraordinary thing called love and feel the depth,
the delight, the ecstasy of it, you will discover that for you the
world is transformed.''
</P>
<P>
   It was an ad for an online travel agent.
</P>
<P>
   _ The latest issue of the Yoga Journal offers some inspiring
advice in an ad for that publication's calendar: ``Inhale. Exhale.
Order.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Daniel Day-Lewis &LR;  is to play  &UR; Henry VIII &LR; , reports W, in
``Henry and Anne,'' a forthcoming movie about the monarch and
 &UR; Anne Boleyn &LR; , who lost her head over him.  &UR; Kate Winslet &LR;  will be
Boleyn. The project starts shooting in England this summer, which
should give Day-Lewis time to start packing in the crumpets _ a De
Niro-like task _ in order to play the king with the 57-inch waist.
</P>
<P>
   _ Two big-time movies will be shot in San Francisco soon:
``Sweet November,'' an action movie starring  &UR; Keanu Reeves &LR; , and
``The Wedding Planner,'' starring  &UR; Jennifer Lopez &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't care who wore it before. There's no way they're going
to look as good as me.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Charlize Theron to designer Randolph Duke, who had informed
her that a dress she had chosen to wear to the Golden Globe awards
ceremony had been worn by another star at the Emmys. Theron was
quoted in New York magazine.
</P>
