 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BOND  &LR; _ With the U.S. government accelerating its plans to
retire its long-term debt, investors in Treasury issues have to
start thinking differently.
</P>
<P>
   The market for Treasuries has turned into an Alice-in-Wonderland
scene, with the yields on shorter-term Treasuries moving higher
than the yields on longer-term Treasuries _ a phenomenon known in
the bond trade as an inverted yield curve. By Arthur M. Louis
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; KANA  &LR; _ Kana Communications, a Redwood City company that helps
firms manage their e-mail, unveiled plans yesterday to spend $4.2
billion for Silknet Software, a New Hampshire firm that uses Web
software to help businesses field questions from customers. By Todd
Wallack
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
