<P>
   BC-MEDIA-TALK-NYT (moved on Sunday, Feb. 6)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Feb. 6,
about the European edition of The Wall Street Journal misstated its
circulation. The Journal sells 16,000 copies in Britain, not
67,000. The total European circulation _ not the total for copies
sold in Europe outside of Britain _ is 83,000.
</P>
