<HEADLINE>
STUDENT SHOT ON COMMUNITY COLLEGE CAMPUS 
</HEADLINE>
  (jw) 
 By RANDAL C. ARCHIBOLD   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   VALHALLA, N.Y. _ A man, apparently enraged over the end of a
relationship, shot a Westchester Community College student Monday
as she fled down the hallway of a campus building. The man then
dashed across campus to a small hill by the student center and
fatally shot himself as a few students watched, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   The woman, Joy Thomas, 18, from Mount Vernon, suffered a gunshot
wound to the forehead. She was listed in critical condition at
Westchester Medical Center, but a police spokesman said the injury
was not life-threatening.
</P>
<P>
   The attacker was in his 20s and was not a student, said
Detective William Rehm, a police spokesman. He did not identify the
man. ``There was an ongoing prior relationship terminated by one
party or the other,'' Rehm said.
</P>
<P>
   The woman was shot about 12:15 p.m., after she and the man
argued in the first-floor hallway of a classroom building, Rehm
said. She turned from the man and walked briskly away, and
realizing that he was following her, she entered an office, asking
for help. The man pulled out a handgun and shot her, Rehm said.
</P>
<P>
   An unidentified employee and a student who were in the office
locked the door after the woman fell, preventing the man from
entering, Rehm said.
</P>
<P>
   The shootings alarmed many on campus, coming in the middle of a
school day and just two days after a 19-year-old Columbia
University sophomore was fatally slashed in her dormitory room. The
suspect in that attack, a 23-year-old man who the police believe
was a former boyfriend of the victim, later jumped to his death in
front of a subway train.
</P>
<P>
   Julius Ford, a vice president of the community college, said
this was the first shooting on the 219-acre campus. Founded in
1946, it has 20,500 students, all of them commuters.
</P>
<ANNOTATION>
   (STORY CAN END HERE. OPTIONAL MATERIAL FOLLOWS)
</ANNOTATION>
<P>
   nn
</P>
</TEXT>
